pageContext.description: Dimensions: L 110.3mm; We 54; Wm 31.7; BM 36.6; Blp 9.1; DS 75.5,Typology: upper m-m with tendency to flattened outer sur.; lower m-m virt. non-existant on rev. side; body angles characterised by narrow neat facets; narrow slit end to socket; constriction at top of loop prob. orig.; change in level of m-m at sides; socket sl. irreg. quadrilateral shape,Manufacture: hmks on lower bl. faces; v. sl. bev. at e. prob. modern cleaning; stump of medium broad cg. fl. down sides - parts rounded, most flattened; cf. fl. also round top of in. - crest flattened with a little associated lipping; no bl. tip hollow.,Condition: e. little nicked, not sharp - browny gold traces suggest recent interference; strong pmks. not particularly regular, in one face - look anc.,Attached Material: v. light buff accretion; mid-brown soil adhering in small patches.
